:: Regulation [event]
One morning while roaming aimlessly around the Presidential Palace garden, Carlotta swiftly approaches you with her usual elegance. "Oh Mr. President, would you mind if I accompany you on your stroll? I do enjoy having someone with me while I take in all the beauty this garden holds."
You smile softly and nod. Together, you and Carlotta walk together talking about a range of topics, including upcoming parties and weddings. Eventually, after enough time has passed, Carlotta shifts the conversation toward something more business related. 
"Mr. President, there are growing concerns about a dwindling workforce nationwide. We are seeing more and more people grow too old to work properly. I've taken the liberty and already spoken with other corporate leaders to find a solution for this problem. Together, we have come to the conclusion that lowering the age requirement for fulltime employment down to 12 years of age would significantly drive up productivity nationally. The Frontiermen are likely to put up some resistance, but I beleive that any effort on their part will fall apart once these younger citizens realize how fullfilling it is to contribute to society." 
You stop walking after her last word, pondering how to respond.

<<link [[1. "Dire times call for dire measures. Once I get back to my office, I'll have someone draft something up declaring the legality of ages 12+ joining the workforce."|Regulation 12]]>> <<set $opinionCarlotta +=1>> <<set $opinionOttovin -= 1>> <</link>>
<<link [[2. "Allowing 12 year old to work just doesn't sit right with me, Carlotta. How about this: I lower the legal hiring age from 18 to 16, that way I'm not sending prepubesant children to the workforce."|Regulation 16]]>> <<set $opinionCarlotta += 0.5>> <<set $opinionOttovin -= 0.5>> <</link>>
<<link [[3. "Children? You want literal children to start working inside mines and factories? I don't mean to be rude Carlotta but that is unacceptable in my eyes."|Regulation same]]>> <<set $opinionCarlotta -= 1>> <</link>>

:: Regulation 12
With her head held high, Carlotta responds, "Oh I am oh so glad you understand the direness of this situation! Don't worry about Ottovin, I'll personally take care of any of his worries concerning this." The two of you continue to converse while walking throughout the garden about the sucess this measure will bring to the nation.
<<include "nextFocus">>
:: Regulation 16
Staring off to the side, Carlotta seems to be pondering your compromise. "Hmmmm, while that is not exactly what I was seeking, I can tell that's the best offer I'm going to get, Mr. President." She pauses for a moment, then carries on. "Okay, I think us Corporate Leaders can make that work. Thank you, Mr. President!" The two of you continue to converse about upcoming events for some time while walking throughout the garden.
<<include "nextFocus">>
:: Regulation same
Staring blankly at you, Carlotta sighs. With tight lips and a half grin, she responds, "Of course, Mr. President." The two of you continue to walk in silence for some time before Carlotta exclaims, "Oh, I almost forgot! I have a board meeting in 30 minutes. I better leave before I'm too late, sir." She grins at you once more, then takes her leave towards a garden exit.
