:: Tax Relief [event]
During a flattery-filled afternoon meeting with Carlotta, she begins to grow more restless in her seat. When you ask her if anything is bothering her, she explains, "Mr. President, I am feeling pressured by the other corporate leaders to propose something to you. I didn't want to be the one to ask, but they thought it be best if it came from me since I'm the most frequent spokesperson of our collective interests when it comes to you." 
"Well... what is it?" you urge. "Sir, its about tax relief. I know, I know, I know! I can hear you sighing within. But in all seriousness, many of your industries are over-taxed by international standards. Any relief at all would alleviate a huge burden."

<<link [[1. "Okay. Send me a list of which industries you feel are overtaxed and I will work through them one by one to determine where taxes can be cut."|Support Tax Relief]]>> <<set $Carlotta += 1>> <<set $playermoney -= 1>> <</link>>
<<link [[2. "Absolutly not. The current corporate tax rate is set in place for a reason and is already quite generous. My government needs the influx of money you and your allies' companies provide. A decrease would only constrain my ability to carry out my presidency."|No Support Tax Relief]]>> <<set $opinionCarlotta -= 1>> <</link>>
<<link [[3. "You insult me, Carlotta. In fact, you insult me to the degree that I genuinly beleive I should raise the corporate tax rate. You and I both know any tax relief would only line the corporate elite's pockets, not help anyone else."|Raise Taxes]]>> <<set $opinionCarlotta -= 2>> <<set $playermoney += 1>> <</link>>

:: Support Tax Relief
"Oh thank you thank you, sir!" Carlotta stands up from her chair with her hands together held up by her chest. "My corporate friends will just love to hear this. I'll have someone send that list over in the coming days." With your permission, she exits the room.
<<include "nextFocus">>
:: No Support Tax Relief
"That's precisely what I told my corporate friends you were going to say," Carlotta admits. "I've heard your opinion on this matter before, but they thought it'd be worth trying. No matter, I'll inform them of your consistency later." In the meantime, you continue to talk about other issues and news with Carlotta.
<<include "nextFocus">>
:: Raise Taxes
Carlotta sighs. "I warned my corporate friends that you might react that way. Very well, I will take my leave and inform interested parties to start preparing for any tax increases." She waits for your nod to leave, then exits the room.
