:: Free Trade [event]
In the past few weeks, picket lines have been formed nationwide calling for an administrative policy change concerning trade with neighboring nations. Ordinary citizens are unusually supportive of a movement to open new markets internationally, which they beleive will create more opportunites for them to grow their wealth.
Late one evening, your advisor enters your office with a concerned look. 
"Mr. President, there has been a new revealation regarding the beginning of this free trade movement. It appears that several corporate heads have intentionally stired up your citizens in order to indirectly pressure you to serve their interests. They likely thought that coming to you directly with this issue would not have successful results, so they took ... an alternative route."
How do you respond to this new development?

<<link [[1. "No matter. While I don't appreicate Carlotta and her corporate allies going behind my back, I have come around to the merits of freer trade. Arrange a TV breifing to the nation. I'll address everyone at once."|Support Free Trade]]>> <<set $opinionCarlotta += 1>> <</link>>
<<link [[2. "I have made my stance on this issue very clear! Freer trade will only lead to job outsourcing. I want Carlotta in my office within the next hour... I need to have a word with her."|No Support Free Trade]]>> <<set $opinionCarlotta -= 2>> <</link>>
<<link [[3. "Please inform Carlotta that I want her in my office within the next hour. I will support this free trade movement, but I will not support her working around me in the slightest."|Support Free Trade Carlotta]]>> <<set $opinionCarlotta -= 1>> <</link>>

:: Support Free Trade
Standing at your podium, you notice the bulb on the camera in front of you shine red. The operator behind dramatically points his finger toward you, giving the indication to begin the address.
"Citzens of this great nation, your voices have been heard loud and clear. After much deliberation these past few weeks, I have found myself changing my position concerning international free trade. This was a very difficult decision to make, but I now intend to open our markets and work closely with neighboring markets with the aim of wealth creation for citizens and corporations alike. Thank you." The red light on the camera dims and you begin to walk away from the podium.
<<include "nextFocus">>
:: No Support Free Trade
Entering you office, Carlotta appears confused about why she was called so suddenly for a meeting.
"Carlotta," you begin, "Would you like to explain to me your influence in what is happening nationwide right now?" She looks at you with wide eyes before responding, "Whatever do you mean, sir?" Slamming you fist on your desk, you yell, "Do not play dumb with me, Carlotta! I know that you and the other corporate heads directly stired up these poor citizens with false-promises of wealth. I will not have my authority worked around! If you seek a change in policy, then you work with me ... not the public."
Turning her head sharply as if wincing with your every word, Carlotta eventually respondes, "Understood, sir. It will not happen again. Might I go?" You stare her dead-on for a moment before relaxing back in your chair stating "You're dismissed." Carlotta quickly turns away and walks through the office door.
<<include "nextFocus">>
:: Support Free Trade Carlotta
Entering you office, Carlotta appears confused about why she was called so suddenly for a meeting.
"Carlotta," you begin, "I wanted you to be the first person of importance to hear that I will be supporting the free trade movement that has swept the nation in recent weeks." She looks at you curiously before stating, "That is very kind of you, sir. I am sure citizens will be happy to hear this." Looking at her blankly, you interupt by clarifying, "However, my support is contingent on you and the other corporate heads coming directly to me in the future, not working around my influence." Pulling her head back slightly, Carlotta says, "What would you be refering to, sir?" Leaning back slowing in your chair, you respond, "Please do not play dumb with me Carlotta. I know you and your allies directly stired up the population with this issue as a way to pressure me. Do not let it happen again."
Realizing that she has been caught, Carlotta nods her head. "Understood, sir. It will not happen again." You nod your head toward the door of your office and Carlotta begins walking out.
